Cakewalk is committed to protecting the privacy of all information provided by our users. Please read the privacy policy below.
Cakewalk collects information (such as mailing and email address) about users during their registration for certain sections of our website.

Cakewalk will not disclose this information to third parties (unless we are required to do so by law) and will protect this information in accordance with our strict security and confidentiality standards.
Cakewalk does not offer or allow the selling of any user provided information to third parties.
Users may opt in to receive information about products, services, clinics, presentations, and other news from us by email.
Users that do not want to receive information from us by email may opt out at any time by visiting this web page http://www.cakewalk.com/newsletter
Security of your Personal Information Cakewalk is committed to protecting the security of your personal information.
We use a variety of security technologies and procedures to help protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
For example, we store the personal information you provide on computer servers with limited access that are located in controlled facilities.

Cookies, Beacons and Tagging We and our vendors may use cookies and other technology such as web beacons or tagging to measure page visits to our site, most frequently viewed pages, the effectiveness of our ads, and to determine the display of content and advertising based on your interests all for the goal of improving your experience with us.
These are anonymous and unidentifiable: They do not include any personal information including your name, address, phone number, email address, or anything that personally identifies you.
Marketo Lastly, we use Marketo cookies to help us create an appealing and engaging experience for you.

If you submit information about yourself like your name, email, or company, Cakewalk may track your interactions with our newsletters and website, allowing us to optimize your experience and receive relevant information.
You can read the Marketo Privacy Policy here. Cakewalk Analytics
Products installed by Cakewalk may contain support for "Cakewalk Analytics."
This data is used to develop the Software further, and to adapt it to user requirements, and to optimize it.
Cakewalk Analytics data will not be shared with any other 3rd party companies outside of Cakewalk Inc. or the Gibson brands.

If the "Cakewalk Analytics" function has been activated in the Software preferences, data about the use of the Software by the user are transferred to us in either anonymous form OR by connecting your Cakewalk account when there is an internet connection.
Further information about Cakewalk Analytics can be found at www.cakewalk.com/analytics. Contact Us
If you have any questions about our Privacy Policy, you may contact us at one of the following addresses: http://www.cakewalk.com/About/contact.aspx
or Cakewalk Attention: Internet Privacy Policy 179 Lincoln Street Boston, MA 02111

Cakewalk is committed to protecting the privacy of all information provided by our users. Please read the privacy policy below.

Cakewalk collects information (such as mailing and email address) about users during their registration for certain sections of our website. Cakewalk will not disclose this information to third parties (unless we are required to do so by law) and will protect this information in accordance with our strict security and confidentiality standards. Cakewalk does not offer or allow the selling of any user provided information to third parties.

Users may opt in to receive information about products, services, clinics, presentations, and other news from us by email. Users that do not want to receive information from us by email may opt out at any time by visiting this web page http://www.cakewalk.com/newsletter

Security of your Personal Information
Cakewalk is committed to protecting the security of your personal information. We use a variety of security technologies and procedures to help protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. For example, we store the personal information you provide on computer servers with limited access that are located in controlled facilities. 
    
Cookies, Beacons and Tagging
We and our vendors may use cookies and other technology such as web beacons or tagging to measure page visits to our site, most frequently viewed pages, the effectiveness of our ads, and to determine the display of content and advertising based on your interests all for the goal of improving your experience with us. These are anonymous and unidentifiable: They do not include any personal information including your name, address, phone number, email address, or anything that personally identifies you.
Marketo
Lastly, we use Marketo cookies to help us create an appealing and engaging experience for you. If you submit information about yourself like your name, email, or company, Cakewalk may track your interactions with our newsletters and website, allowing us to optimize your experience and receive relevant information. You can read the Marketo Privacy Policy here.
Cakewalk Analytics 

        Products installed by Cakewalk may contain support for "Cakewalk Analytics." This data is used to develop the Software further, and to adapt it to user requirements, and to optimize it. Cakewalk Analytics data will not be shared with any other 3rd party companies outside of Cakewalk Inc. or the Gibson brands.

If the “Cakewalk Analytics“ function has been activated in the Software preferences, data about the use of the Software by the user are transferred to us in either anonymous form OR by connecting your Cakewalk account when there is an internet connection. Further information about Cakewalk Analytics can be found at www.cakewalk.com/analytics.
    
Contact Us

      If you have any questions about our Privacy Policy, you may contact us at one of the following addresses:
      
http://www.cakewalk.com/About/contact.aspx 

      or
      
      Cakewalk 
      Attention: Internet Privacy Policy 
      179 Lincoln Street 
      Boston, MA 02111
